pulltitle: Render both views on a single page
pullsbody:
Fixes #75 - No need for a router library at this point, we only have 2 views (`zero_coverage` & `browser`).

This PR removes the `zero_coverage_report.html` file, and merge its content with `index.html`
The inner links are updated, the app is always using the same context (no reload between zero coverage & browser mode)

Supported hashes:

- `/` or `/index.html` without hash, loads the coverage for mozilla-central at latest revision
- `/#deadbeef:path/to/dir`: loads the coverage for folder `path/to/dir` at revision `deadbeef` (default to latest)
- `/#deadbeef:path/to/file.cpp`: loads the coverage for file `path/to/file` at revision `deadbeef` (default to latest)
- `/#zero:path/to/dir`: loads the zero coverage for folder `path/to/dir`
